product.productName: Classic Triumph Daytona 1000. A rare bike, recently rebuilt.
product.description: Here we have my rebuilt 1991 (but first registered 1993) Triumph Daytona 1000 in what they've called Assam Black. This bike is in really good condition, having been rebuilt by me over the winter months. I bought it as a bit of a wreck last September and have spent the last five months bringing it back to life and putting it on the road. It was in a real state and some real 'nuts and bolts' work has been done, like replacing rotted subframes and, of course, horrible jobs like greasing the swingarm bearings have all been done. I didn't rebuild the engine (I thought I'd leave that until this coming winter) and it's still not perfect, but it's really good, and it's certainly a lot of fun to ride, especially since I rebuilt the front forks and made sure that the front suspension is all ok. To give an idea of what's been done and what's been spent, I've copied below the details from the file I kept. Some of this is for tools which I needed, but most of it is stuff which is now on the machine: 23-Oct-15 Cost of bike 650 23-Oct-15 Man with van 80 04-Nov-15 De greaser 6.21 06-Nov-15 m/c screws 2.95 10-Nov-15 throttle cable 12.85 10-Nov-15 Radiator guard 13.74 13-Nov-15 Carb spray 9.4 13-Nov-15 Gearchange rubber/Pushrod assembly etc 34.4 15-Nov-15 Chain breaker 11.58 18-Nov-15 Solenoid Bracket 13.98 18-Nov-15 Battery box bracket 13.98 18-Nov-15 Centre stand plates & springs 9 22-Nov-15 Carb rebuild stuff 89.88 29-Nov-15 36mm socket 7.49 29-Nov-15 30" breaker bar 11.99 30-Nov-15 K & N filter/Chain/Sprockets 142.53 06-Dec-15 Swing arm pivot bolt 6.75 07-Dec-15 Degreaser 4.85 07-Dec-15 Seals/Grease nipple covers 18.52 08-Dec-15 Red grease 8.9 08-Dec-15 Rear suspension linkage 22.99 13-Dec-15 Engine case bolts 15 15-Dec-15 Centre stand 52.98 16-Dec-15 Bolts/Locknuts/retaining rings 24.4 17-Dec-15 Exhaust hangers 16.95 19-Dec-15 Rear brake m/c 28.8 19-Dec-15 SBS Rear brake pads 18.99 19-Dec-15 Chain riveter 7.99 19-Dec-15 rear brake seal kit 20.5 27-Dec-15 Oil feed pipes OEM 50 30-Dec-15 Cam seal kit & rear M/c 33.94 03-Jan-16 Oil coller bracket 25 10-Jan-16 Battery 87.93 10-Jan-16 Qximiser leads 8.99 16-Jan-16 Oil Cooler 43.94 17-Jan-16 Cambi spanners 4.75 22-Jan-16 battery strap/Grommets/Gaskets 22.77 22-Jan-16 Nosecone subframe 36.98 26-Jan-16 Black paint 6.97 26-Jan-16 Acrylic clear coat 7.49 28-Jan-16 Caliper pinch bolts 6.99 30-Jan-16 Fork caps & seals 96.39 31-Jan-16 Fork oil 9.88 04-Feb-16 Front brake seal kit 48 08-Feb-16 Dremel brushes 10.75 10-Feb-16 Rear hugger 45 10-Feb-16 Front calipers 78.99 11-Feb-16 SBS Front brake pads 34.99 20-Feb-16 Indicator Relay 11.99 23-Feb-16 MOT and Chain Rivet (Ian Murray) 42.85 24-Feb-16 Decals/Mirror spacer 25.74 26-Feb-16 Tubular top rack 79.99 27-Feb-16 Sea foam 15.95 28-Feb-16 Cockpit infil panels 9.99 28-Feb-16 LHS Fairing infil 9.99 06-Mar-16 Union flag decals 3.98 06-Mar-16 Footpeg rubbers & bolts 14.9 TOTAL 2232.73 I'm speculatively starting to hunt around for a tourer, because I'm hatching plans for the summer. In the past, I've owned Honda Pans and BMW RTs so I know those bikes pretty well. So, if you've got something of similar value and you think you might be looking to change for something a bit different, please get in touch. But I'm not in a big rush to change and please don't ask me to swap for anything worth less than what I've spent. I could actually go touring on this quite happily I think, but I thought I'd test the water and see what's about. If I do end up keeping it, I'd be looking to replace the tupperware and strip and rebuild the engine this coming winter. Triumph only made a few hundred of these and there can't be many left on the road now, especially in this sort of condition. I reckon it'll only go up in value. I've got the V5 and it's MOTd until February 2017. It's got dealer service stamps to 33,000 miles, and it's currently got 67000 on the clock. I should say that, since I took the photos just after its MOT, I have put new decals on the lower fairing so those are good again now. there are still some marks on the fairings themselves, but they're not too horrendous! Am looking for a tourer (Honda Pan, BMW RT) or an Adventure bike (V-strom etc) Thanks for looking.

product.productName: 2007 Honda CBR 125R for sale, only 8000 on clock!
product.description: Selling on behalf of my brother, we have for sale a 2007 CBR 125R with only 8000 on the clock. There have been 6 registered keepers of the bike, but two of these are me! I have owned the bike (twice) since 2014. As expected with a 125 learner bike and a bike of this age, it does have some cosmetic damage which we have tried to show in the pictures. It has some chips and a dent to the tank, it had some cracks to the fairings, a scuff on the front light and the indicators are secured with tape. It also has a slightly sticky gear selector. I have loved this bike in the time I have owned it, hence owning it twice! It was well looked after and serviced at the back end of 2014 with only approx. 1000 miles added to it since. In the time I have owned the bike, the chain, sprocket and spindle have been replaced, the chain regularly lubed and it has been regularly cleaned. It has both keys and alarm fobs, I will also throw the Oxford lock. I used this bike to pass my test and now ride a 650, hence the sale as it is no longer required. It is a great learner bike, fun to ride and one of the best looking 125's around (in my opinion). These bikes do hold their value, but considering the cosmetic damage this has reflected in the price. I am looking in the region of £1200, but will consider reasonable offers. It is currently on SORN, with the MOT expiring on the 16th May 2016, I see no reason why this would not fly through its next MOT. Due to working shifts, my sister will deal with any initial queries but I am happy for anyone to come and take a look at the bike at mutual convenience. The bike is in Stevenage, Hertfordshire. More photos available on request.

product.description: Triumph Thunderbird 900-1995 Carb Model- Totally Overhauled -New Sprag Clutch. Triumph's Thunderbird 900 Triple - A 1995 Appreciating Classic Benefitting from recently completed 'No Budget' Comprehensive Refurbishment. Restored with no restraint to Expenditure on Parts & Labour. Complimented by many Enhancing Improvements using mainly Triumph Quality Parts. Show the amount of meticulous work undertaken to bring it back to it's present condition. This Thunderbird was Completely Stripped Down. All parts individually cleaned - refurbished - upgraded or replaced. Engine removed & stripped down for a check over & installation of a 'New Sprag Clutch'. Crank Case re-sprayed, all New Gaskets & Seals. New S/S Manifold Studs & Nuts, New spark plugs. Casings polished. New Ignition pick up & Three Brand New Coils. New K&N oil filter, Fresh Semi/ Synthetic Engine Oil, Carburettors cleaned inside & out I also had a Stage 1-3 Jet Kit made up specifically for this bike by 'Sigma U.S.A'. carbs then re-assembled with all New Seals, float levels re-set, carbs balanced. new K&N air filter. & New Throttle Cable. --- Read 'Sigma's statement :- This is not just some jets in a box, where you get to guess at what you need, and pull your carburettor 10 times trying to figure it out, it is a comprehensive Custom Engineered 6Sigma Jet Kit, addressing all throttle positions, throttle response. Each kit is Custom Engineered by 6Sigma to your bike and its modifications. Replacing just the jets does not address 1/4-3/4 throttle, or throttle response, only full throttle. This Kit is for all throttle positions, and throttle response. This is a tuner kit, to get everything out of your bike, that it can give. The removed clutch slave cleaned sprayed & Re-built it with New piston & seals. Drive sprocket checked out good as did rear sprocket. Chain Cleaned & all good. Swing Arm & Suspension Spring cleaned & checked out Pivots Greased. Rear mudguard cleaned underside & re-sprayed. A New Number Plate is on re-furbed brackets. Many Old Nuts Bolts Washers etc replaced with Stainless Steel as available & appropriate. Both Brake Callipers stripped cleaned & re-built with new seals new S/S Pad Retainer Pin + Plug plus Bleed Nipples & New Nissan Disc Pads. New Rear Disc - Both discs have New S/S disc bolts, S/S Braided lines to Both Brakes & Clutch. New Adjustable Brake & Clutch Levers. All Three Master Cylinders Stripped Cleaned & Rebuilt with New Full Service kits & S/S cap screws. Both front Masters re-sprayed black after the fitting of new clear glass to inspection ports. Front forks stripped for installation of Taper Roller Bearings to Top & Bottom Yokes which were cleaned & re-sprayed, fork legs drained & flushed, Progressive Springs Installed with fresh Shell Advanced Fork Oil. Bottom Legs cleaned & re- sprayed with Clear Lacquer. Alloy Wheel rims polished. Both Wheels have Stainlees Steel Spokes, & new dust seals. New Matching 'AVON' Road Rider Tyres with New Heavy Duty Inner Tubes. Front mudguard-brace cleared of debris + w/proofed & sealed. refit with S/S Bolts plus a new Fender Extender. Front rebuilt Calliper has new S/S fixing bolts. Instrument units stripped + cleaned. Chrome Headlight re-sprayed Inside. All harness connections opened cleaned & treated with ACF-50 as were the battery box fuse box ECU etc. Starter Motor removed checked re sprayed connections cleaned & new case seal, Alternator removed re sprayed & installed with New Cush Rubber kit. Fuel tank valve serviced & filter cleaned. Tank is clean & sound. Radiator cleaned internally & out / repainted as necessary. Fan / Thermostat / water pump / all removed cleaned & checked. System checked sound with fresh Correct Anti Freeze / Distilled water mix. Both Side Stand & Center Stand are in excellent order. Despite being in good condition I had the Triumph King & Queen saddle Professionally upgraded with New Quality Cloth buttons & red piping/stitching, only back panel reused (it has Triumph Imprinted). The Battery is recent & has an Optimate Connector. The retained Original Exhaust System's S/S headers were cleaned of old chrome & are now VHT Sprayed Matt Black, & fitted with New Short Megaphone Silencers, these are easily altered by simple baffle & or wadding removal, via end cap. Originals also come with the bike, as do the last seven years M.O.T's that show mileage continuation & no advisories. Now on 03-11-15 completed, it has a fresh M.O.T. A opportunity to purchase a bike to show and/or as an investment. This 1976 Honda ST70 Monkeybike has had a complete strip down, nut and bolt restoration (using genuine Honda spares) with no expense spared. They are, however ever increasing in rarity and value. This unique bike was displayed recently on Morton's concours stand at the Stafford Motorcycle Mechanics Bike show over the weekend of 17th & 18th October and attracted a lot of interest (regrettably "for sale" signs are not allowed on the concourse display). One of the advantages of these bikes is that they can be transported in most large cars/estates. product.description: For Sale are 2 Moto Guzzi Zigolo's. Both have V5C Registration Documents and both are registered in my name. I have owned both of these bikes for many many years. The 110cc was registered in 1957 and the 98cc was registered in 1960. INFO ABOUT THE 110cc The 110cc in quite nice condition with V5c. I put it back together last year as my son said he would like it but has now decided he wants a car. I had it running after putting it back together last year, but since then it has not been started. The seat has been recovered and never used. Most of these parts came from Stanley Woods. ex TT winner and Moto Guzzi Dealer in Ireland in the 1980s / 90s. The frame and engine numbers do not match but the original engine with matching numbers to the frame comes with it. This engine is dismantled, so needs rebuilding. The paintwork and chrome are OK but not perfect. In the picture the bike is stood on a concrete block. The centre stand is with it but needs a new return spring fitting. It needs headlight and tail light bulbs. It needs an exhaust gasket. It needs a speedo drive/cable. There are 4 new Moto Guzzi transfers. 2 new Zigolo 110cc transfers. 110cc engine gasket set (partly used) INFO ABOUT THE 98cc Parts that I have that have also been stored away in my loft :- Frame with V5C Swinging arm. That I am more than sure that the rest of the bike don't come close to the same condition, including the engine and all wearable parts, frame and so forth. If not sold, I will just keep it being messed around way too much by time wasters for no reason, yes I will have the bike, I will be at yours on Sat, I will be at yours on Tuesday, I will take it for sure on Friday don't sell it, and list is endless, to then not turn up and mess up my day and plans for no reason. All the email and questions/interest I am getting for my Honda is getting a bit ridiculous now, just come down and take a look at the bike and see me in person, if it's one of these great classic Honda's you are looking for, to collect or ride you will not in anyway be disappointed with this one for sure, it's a proper 33 year old genuine bike that has been well taken care of and has had no end of upkeep work done by the same owner for that past 28 years. All that out of the way finally, this is my ad for my mint Honda :))))))) To all the classic Honda enthusiasts, I have for sale a beautiful machine, that I agreed to take px for my like brand new Yamaha that I had to sell due to personal reasons. I decided to do the deal has I have not seen one of these great machines in this condition since I was around 8 years old, and that is going back a bit. Classic 82 reg Honda Nighthawk 650 cc, low mileage, same caring owner for the past 28 years. I will start by saying that the photos were taken on a miserable day, and they really don't do the bike justice, this bike is in fantastic condition for 33 year old and very well cared for and maintained. I would go so far as to say, one of the best remaining examples of a UK non import Honda Nighthawk 650 cc left in the country, not only a rare, but very rare in this great condition. Where to start with this bike that looks great. 1) Chrome all around in great condition 2) Frame in great condition 3) Fairings in great condition 4) New spark plugs and lines 5) Battery in good working order and fairly new. 6) New tyres back and front 7) Engine starts and runs spot on every time. 8) All electrics in fully working order 9) Brakes work as they should 10) Forks are in great condition and new seals not long back. I have seen these bikes on eBay sell for £1200 to £1400 in very poor condition, very high milage and has spare and repair. This one is in fantastic condition, low milage and well worth my asking price. £1800 ono.................Sensible offers and possible px welcome.
